% ============================================================
\subsection*{Short Background}
% ============================================================

\subsubsection*{The project}

The \#TERRA project examines pro-environmental attitudes and behaviors during adolescence, with a focus on the individual and contextual factors that shape them. It combines a nationwide cross-sectional study with a longitudinal approach to track developmental changes and daily variations in ecological behavior. The main goals are:

\begin{itemize}
  \item Develop and validate tools to measure these attitudes and behaviors in areas like sustainable consumption, waste management, and energy efficiency.
  \item Identify the main factors that shape adolescents' pro-environmental attitudes and behaviors.
  \item Examine how these attitudes and behaviors evolve during adolescence and what predicts change.
  \item Analyze daily fluctuations considering personal factors (e.g., mood, life satisfaction) and immediate social and environmental contexts.
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection*{This document}

This dissemination strategy is a guide for action that presents the strategy for communication and dissemination of \#TERRA. First, we present the project identity (logo) to establish the basic principles to preserve visual properties and facilitate the correct dissemination, perception, identification, and memorization of the \#TERRA communication material. Next, we present the goals of the communication strategy and the dissemination tools of \#TERRA.

% ============================================================
\section{Introduction}
% ============================================================

\subsection{About the Project}

The \#TERRA project aims to investigate Pro-Environmental (PE) attitudes and behaviors during adolescence, seeking to identify their individual and contextual antecedents. This project combines a cross-sectional analysis of adolescents' PE attitudes and behaviors, based on a representative sample of the Portuguese population, with a longitudinal analysis focused on individual changes associated with age and daily fluctuations in ecological behaviors. This project aims to:

\begin{enumerate}[label=(\arabic*)]
  \item develop, adapt, and validate assessment instruments that reliably and validly measure PE attitudes and behaviors in adolescence, encompassing both the perceptual and general dimensions of actions, as well as their frequency and nature within ecologically relevant domains such as sustainable consumption, waste management, and energy efficiency;
  \item characterize and identify the main individual and contextual factors that shape the PE attitudes and behaviors of Portuguese adolescents;
  \item examine the developmental trajectory of PE attitudes and behaviors throughout adolescence, identifying predictive and risk factors associated with interindividual changes;
  \item analyze daily and weekly fluctuations in adolescents' ecologically relevant behaviors, investigating the role of intraindividual predictors (e.g., mood states and life satisfaction) and immediate contextual factors (e.g., daily social and environmental context) that shape variations in these behaviors.
\end{enumerate}

Taken together, research results will enrich research in basic psychology, through a deeper understanding of the complex interaction between individual and contextual predictors of PE attitudes and behaviors, providing critical evidence to promote environmentally sustainable behaviors among young people. The \#TERRA project will also have a significant social impact, with direct implications across multiple intervention domains. In the educational domain, it will support the design of educational programs aimed at promoting sustainable behaviors, contributing to more effective pedagogical practices in fostering environmentally responsible citizens. In the domain of public policy, the findings will provide solid scientific guidance for national climate change mitigation strategies, enabling more informed decisions aligned with the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). Furthermore, the \#TERRA project will impact social awareness by offering evidence to underpin campaigns that strengthen active environmental citizenship and encourage the adoption of more responsible consumption habits.

\subsection{Visual Identity: Logo}

The logo of the \#TERRA project combines two main elements:

\begin{itemize}
  \item The project name, ``\#TERRA'', is written in bold letters with a hashtag that emphasizes its social and digital dimension.
  \item A symbolic image of a water droplet enclosing a globe, representing the link between Earth and sustainability. The droplet suggests caring for natural resources, while the globe highlights the global scope of ecological challenges.
\end{itemize}

The logo is available in four versions:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Green or gradient version} -- conveys nature, growth, and ecological responsibility.
  \item \textbf{Black-and-white version} -- ideal for high-contrast applications and minimalist contexts.
  \item \textbf{Gradient version with tagline} -- includes ``Paths to Sustainability in Adolescence,'' reinforcing the project's focus on youth and sustainability.
  \item \textbf{Black-and-white version with tagline} -- for simple, formal, or monochromatic materials.
\end{itemize}

