\subsection{Utilization}

The \#TERRA logo should be used for all official communications of the project, namely the website, social media, communication material, reports, and external communications. The logo can be scaled to publications, flyers, and other materials. However, using the logo in too small a format is not recommended, as it would no longer be recognizable.

\subsection{Funding Organization}

In accordance with the provisions outlined in the Rules for Participation, the \#TERRA research team undertakes to explicitly recognize COMPETE 2030 and PORTUGAL 2030 as the project's funding organizations, as well as the European Union as a co-funder of the project. The research team undertakes to communicate these programmes in all project-related communications, activities, documents, and materials, as well as at any promotional events relating to the project. This includes, without limitation, the annual report, website content, emails, social media posts, digital materials, and communications on social networks.

