% ============================================================
\section{Dissemination Strategy Guide}
% ============================================================

This Dissemination Strategy Guide outlines the approach for planning, targeting, developing, and implementing communication and dissemination actions throughout the \#TERRA project. Special attention will be given to promoting and sharing project results and ensuring accurate and timely information flow among the research team, advisory panel, stakeholders, and, most importantly, the broader community. The \#TERRA project views research as a tool for environmental awareness. Therefore, measures will be taken to strengthen the connection between science and society, fostering dialogue and engagement with adolescents, educators, policymakers, and the community. This plan defines the project's dissemination objectives and the actions required to achieve them. It establishes priorities and key goals, identifies main stakeholders, and specifies the most effective channels and tools for outreach. It also sets timelines for planned dissemination activities and stakeholder engagement, ensuring that communication efforts are strategic, inclusive, and impactful.

This Dissemination Strategy Guide covers both internal and external communication.

\subsection{Internal Communication}

Internal communication aims to maintain transparency, collaboration, and timely information exchange among team members and partners. The following mechanisms will be implemented:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Email Communication:} All official internal communication will use the dedicated project email: \href{mailto:terra@fpce.up.pt}{terra@fpce.up.pt}.
  \item \textbf{Virtual and Presential Meetings:} Regular videoconferences and in-person meetings will be scheduled to discuss progress, address challenges, and plan upcoming activities.
  \item \textbf{Data Storage and Sharing:} Project data and documents will be securely stored and shared through the University of Porto Server and Center for Psychology at the University of Porto Network Attached Storage (NAS). These platforms ensure compliance with institutional data protection policies and facilitate collaborative work.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{External Communication}

External communication focuses on disseminating project results, promoting engagement, and ensuring visibility among diverse audiences, including adolescents, educators, policymakers, researchers, and the community. The following channels and actions will be implemented:

\begin{itemize}
  \item Project Website
  \item Project Social Media
  \item Open Science Framework (OSF)
  \item Participation in Scientific Events and Publications
  \item Infographics and Press Releases
  \item White Book and Closing Seminar
\end{itemize}

These channels and actions aim to guarantee that the project's outputs are accessible, transparent, and impactful.

\subsubsection{Project Website}

The first version of the project website is already available at: \href{https://projeto-terra.fpce.up.pt/en/home/}{projeto-terra.fpce.up.pt}. The website is bilingual (Portuguese and English), ensuring accessibility for both national and international audiences. It serves as the main hub for external communication and includes the following pages:

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Project:} A visually appealing banner featuring the project logo and tagline ``Paths to Sustainability in Adolescence'', reinforcing the project's identity and mission. The homepage also provides a summary of the project's objectives, allowing visitors to quickly understand its purpose and scope.
  \item \textbf{Team:} Short bios for each team member including institutional affiliations and ORCID, highlighting their expertise and role in the project. It also includes profiles of all Advisory Panel members, ensuring transparency and recognition of their contribution.
  \item \textbf{Announcements:} A dedicated page for announcements, events, and progress reports. This section will showcase key milestones, participation in conferences, and activities relevant to both academic and general audiences.
  \item \textbf{Stakeholders:} This page will present the strategic community partners involved in the project. It will highlight organizations and institutions that collaborate with \#TERRA to promote sustainability in adolescence, ensuring visibility and recognition of their role in supporting the project's objectives.
\end{itemize}

